annotationA: 60S ribosomal protein L3; The L3 protein is a component of the large subunit of cytoplasmic ribosomes
annotationB: Ribosomal protein L30, isoform B; Structural constituent of ribosome. It is involved in the biological process described with: peripheral nervous system development; mitotic spindle elongation; translation; growth; centrosome duplication; mitotic spindle organization
